title: Magnitude 4.2 earthquake strikes near Belfair, Washington
text:
The United States Geological Survey reports a preliminary magnitude 4.2 earthquake struck near Belfair, Washington on Wednesday.
The quake hit at 8:59 PM local time at a depth of 16 kilometers.
There was no initial word on damage or injury resulting from the quake. More information on this earthquake is available on the USGS event page .
